THE CONTESTANTS.

07:35.756 --> 07:37.891
BUT DON'T FRET, BOYS,
YOU CAN STILL SIGN UP

07:37.925 --> 07:40.227
TO DROP TROU AND WIN A THOU.

07:40.260 --> 07:43.864
ALL RIGHT, OUR FIRST CONTESTANT
IS "FOUR ALARM FRED."

07:43.897 --> 07:47.134
HE'LL, UH, LIGHT YOUR FIRE
AND PUT IT OUT.

07:47.167 --> 07:48.636
[cheers and applause]

07:48.669 --> 07:56.610
*

08:09.289 --> 08:12.125
- SHAVED CHEST, PEC IMPLANTS.

08:12.159 --> 08:13.861
STEROIDS.

08:13.894 --> 08:15.729
HAIR CLUB FOR MEN.

08:15.763 --> 08:17.598
- YEAH, IT'S SAD, ISN'T IT?

08:17.631 --> 08:18.966
ALL THESE OLDER GUYS,

08:18.999 --> 08:22.035
STILL PARTYING
WAY PAST THEIR PRIME.

08:22.069 --> 08:23.904
THEY DON'T KNOW WHEN TO STOP.

08:23.937 --> 08:26.139
- OH.

08:26.173 --> 08:29.276
- SO HOW ABOUT THE REAL THING?

08:29.309 --> 08:31.745
- CHECK BACK WITH ME
IN AN HOUR.

08:31.779 --> 08:33.280
- WHAT?

08:33.313 --> 08:36.617
SO NOW I'M A BACKUP PLAN.

08:36.650 --> 08:38.552
WHO YOU DO
WHEN ALL ELSE FAILS?

08:38.586 --> 08:42.189
- HOW MANY TIMES DO I HAVE TO
TELL YOU, WE'RE NOT A COUPLE.

08:42.222 --> 08:45.225
MICHAEL AND DAVID
ARE A COUPLE.

08:45.258 --> 08:46.794
LINDSAY AND MELANIE
ARE A COUPLE.

08:46.827 --> 08:48.261
TED AND WHAT'S-HIS-NAME
ARE A COUPLE.

08:48.295 --> 08:50.831
- YEAH, SO WHAT ARE WE,
BRIAN?

08:50.864 --> 08:53.901
- I DON'T KNOW ABOUT YOU,
BUT I'M SINGLE.

08:53.934 --> 09:01.942
*

09:14.121 --> 09:17.190
- THE INFORMATION DESK
AT THE NORTH END OF THE MALL.

09:17.224 --> 09:19.993
YOUR SON JONATHAN IS
WAITING FOR YOU.

09:22.930 --> 09:24.865
- HEY.

09:27.067 --> 09:28.268
- HELLO.

09:45.018 --> 09:49.857
- SO WHAT ARE YOU INTO?

09:49.890 --> 09:52.993
- A LITTLE SHOPPING.

09:53.026 --> 09:55.863
DINNER, A MOVIE.

09:55.896 --> 09:59.066
THE NEW JULIA ROBERTS.

09:59.099 --> 10:02.770
I JUST LOVE HER.

10:02.803 --> 10:06.273
- YOU, UH,
WANT TO DO SOMETHING?

10:13.013 --> 10:17.918
- I'M SORRY, BUT PUBLIC
RESTROOMS AREN'T MY SCENE.

10:17.951 --> 10:19.887
[zips fly]

10:19.920 --> 10:22.690
- THEN HOW ABOUT WE GO
SOMEPLACE ELSE?

10:25.458 --> 10:27.828
*

10:27.861 --> 10:30.230
- GOD, THE MUSIC'S
SO LOUD IN HERE.

10:30.263 --> 10:31.799
YOU CAN BARELY
HEAR YOURSELF THINK.

10:31.832 --> 10:33.000
[music stops]

10:33.033 --> 10:35.202
OH, THAT'S BETTER.

10:35.235 --> 10:37.705
I DON'T KNOW WHY I INSISTED
ON COMING HERE.

10:37.738 --> 10:38.972
IT'S ALWAYS THE SAME.

10:39.006 --> 10:41.341
THE GUYS WHO ARE INTERESTED IN
ME, I'M NOT INTERESTED IN THEM.

10:41.374 --> 10:45.278
AND THE ONES I'M INTERESTED IN,
WELL, AREN'T INTERESTED IN ME.

10:45.312 --> 10:46.313
AHH.

10:46.346 --> 10:51.418
*

10:51.451 --> 10:54.955
[classical music]

10:54.988 --> 11:02.996
*

11:12.205 --> 11:13.306
[synchronized finger snaps]

11:19.379 --> 11:22.049
- GENTLEMEN AND GENTLEMEN,

11:22.082 --> 11:26.119
CONTESTANT NUMBER TWO,
OFFICER O'REILLY.

11:26.153 --> 11:29.122
HE'S VERY ARRESTING,
DON'T YOU THINK?

11:29.156 --> 11:31.491
OFFICER, I JUST GOT
A PARKING TICKET.

11:31.524 --> 11:33.026
STRIP-SEARCH ME!

11:33.060 --> 11:40.801
*

11:40.834 --> 11:43.036
- THE PROBLEM WITH THIS CONTEST
IS THAT IT EXPOSES

11:43.070 --> 11:46.874
THE SINGLE, MOST TRAGIC FLAW
OF GAY CULTURE.

11:46.907 --> 11:49.042
- IT EXPOSES A LOT MORE
THAN THAT, DOC.

11:49.076 --> 11:51.979
- AND THAT IS OUR ALMOST
PATHOLOGICAL OBSESSION

11:52.012 --> 11:56.249
WITH YOUTH, BEAUTY,
AND SMOOTH, MUSCULAR BODIES.

11:56.283 --> 11:58.018
- I KNOW, WHAT A SHAME.

11:58.051 --> 11:59.787
- AND UNTIL WE BREAK FREE
OF OUR STUNTED ADOLESCENCE

11:59.820 --> 12:01.822
AND OUR SUPERFICIAL VALUES,

12:01.855 --> 12:03.490
WE'LL ALWAYS BE BOYS,
NEVER MEN.

12:03.523 --> 12:05.325
- GOD, IS THAT ALL?

12:05.358 --> 12:07.127
- I HAPPEN TO FIND
WHAT DAVID IS SAYING

12:07.160 --> 12:08.461
TO BE PROFOUNDLY INSIGHTFUL.

12:08.495 --> 12:12.332
- I FIND IT TO BE
PROFOUNDLY FULL OF SHIT.

12:12.365 --> 12:14.034
AN OPINION PUT FORTH AS TRUTH

12:14.067 --> 12:16.536
BY A BUNCH OF
HYPOCRITICAL, JEALOUS,

12:16.569 --> 12:20.073
GUILT-RIDDEN, SELF-LOATHING,
MIDDLE-AGED,

12:20.107 --> 12:21.541
SEXUALLY FRUSTRATED,

12:21.574 --> 12:24.878
PSEUDO-INTELLECTUAL FAGS
WHO WISH THEY WERE STRAIGHT.

12:24.912 --> 12:26.914
- [laughs]

12:26.947 --> 12:29.516
*

12:29.549 --> 12:31.985
- SHOW ME!

12:32.019 --> 12:33.787
[cheers and applause]

12:33.821 --> 12:36.957
*

12:36.990 --> 12:40.327
- DO IT!

12:40.360 --> 12:42.562
- SO WHY DON'T YOU SIGN UP?

12:42.595 --> 12:44.197
- 'CAUSE I DON'T NEED TO
DANCE AROUND IN MY UNDERWEAR

12:44.231 --> 12:45.933
TO GET LAID.

12:45.966 --> 12:49.436
- OR MAYBE YOU CAN'T HANDLE
THE COMPETITION.

12:49.469 --> 12:52.439
[chuckles]

13:00.513 --> 13:03.150
- OH, MY GOD,
HE'S GOING TO SIGN UP.

13:03.183 --> 13:04.284
- NO, HE WON'T.

13:04.317 --> 13:06.086
NO WAY.

13:06.119 --> 13:10.257
- HE IS.

13:10.290 --> 13:12.960
- OUR NEXT CONTESTANT
IS MOHAMMED.

13:12.993 --> 13:16.496
HE'S A MASTER YOGA INSTRUCTOR
FROM RIPT GYM.

13:16.529 --> 13:19.032
HE CAN PERFORM
"AUTO FELLATIO."

13:19.066 --> 13:20.267
WHAT THE FUCK'S THAT?

13:20.300 --> 13:22.235
IF THAT'S GIVING A BLOW JOB
IN YOUR CAR,

13:22.269 --> 13:23.837
THEN I'M A MASTER TOO.

13:23.871 --> 13:26.039
[laughter]

13:26.073 --> 13:29.843
[cheers and applause]

13:29.877 --> 13:37.817
*

13:55.502 --> 13:57.938
SHIT, I'M STARTING TO WILT,
AND I'VE STILL GOT

13:57.971 --> 14:01.241
THE BEST PECS CONTEST
AT BOYTOY TOMORROW.

14:01.274 --> 14:04.377
MM, WHAT'S WITH THE LONG FACE,
SWEETHEART?

14:04.411 --> 14:08.648
- NOTHING.

14:08.681 --> 14:09.649
THIS GUY.

14:09.682 --> 14:13.520
- HMM. AIN'T IT ALWAYS?

14:13.553 --> 14:15.255
SO WHAT DID THIS GUY DO?

14:15.288 --> 14:17.224
- HE TAKES ME FOR GRANTED.

14:17.257 --> 14:19.659
- A WALKING WET DREAM LIKE YOU
COULD HAVE ANYONE HE WANTS.

14:19.692 --> 14:21.261
- I KNOW.

14:21.294 --> 14:24.497
THAT'S THE PART I FIND
SO IRRITATING.

14:24.531 --> 14:27.000
- MAYBE HE NEEDS TO KNOW IT.

14:30.270 --> 14:33.473
MAYBE EVERYBODY
NEEDS TO KNOW IT.

14:33.506 --> 14:36.243
- HEY, DEB. TELEPHONE.

14:36.276 --> 14:37.978
- IF IT'S PUBLISHER'S
CLEARING HOUSE,

14:38.011 --> 14:40.113
TELL THEM I WON THE SWEEPSTAKES
LAST YEAR.

14:40.147 --> 14:41.248
- IT'S YOUR BROTHER.

14:41.281 --> 14:45.018
- OH!

14:45.052 --> 14:47.154
HEY, VIC.
WHAT'S UP, HONEY?

14:47.187 --> 14:49.356
- DON'T PANIC.
I'VE BEEN ARRESTED.

14:49.389 --> 14:50.457
- WHAT?

14:50.490 --> 14:52.559
- I SAID DON'T PANIC.
- ALL RIGHT.

14:52.592 --> 14:56.129
- AND DON'T TELL ANYBODY.
NOBODY. NOT EVEN MICHAEL.

14:56.163 --> 14:58.265
- WHAT HAPPENED?

14:58.298 --> 15:01.068
- I WAS AT THE MALL,
I WENT TO PEE.

15:01.101 --> 15:05.105
- WELL, WHAT ARE THEY CHARGING
YOU WITH, NOT FLUSHING?

15:05.138 --> 15:08.275
- INDECENT EXPOSURE.

15:08.308 --> 15:10.510
- INDECENT--

15:10.543 --> 15:12.412
WHAT THE HELL'D YOU DO,
WAG IT AT SOMEBODY?

15:12.445 --> 15:16.383
- I DIDN'T DO ANYTHING,
SIS, I SWEAR.

15:16.416 --> 15:18.351
CAN YOU COME DOWN?

15:18.385 --> 15:21.388
I'M AT THE ZONE 8 STATION
ON LIBERTY AND GRANT.

15:21.421 --> 15:22.722
- I'M LEAVING RIGHT NOW,
ALL RIGHT?

15:22.755 --> 15:25.325
JUST STAY CALM.
- AND COULD YOU BRING MY MEDS?

15:25.358 --> 15:28.428
I SHOULD'VE TAKEN THEM
AN HOUR AGO.

15:28.461 --> 15:30.030
- YEAH, DON'T WORRY.

15:30.063 --> 15:31.231
DON'T WORRY ABOUT ANYTHING.

15:31.264 --> 15:32.432
- PLEASE, SIT DOWN.

15:32.465 --> 15:34.134
- YEAH, SIT DOWN.
YOU TOO, SIT.

15:37.604 --> 15:41.241
*

15:41.274 --> 15:43.276
[classical music]

15:43.310 --> 15:45.212
- I CAN'T EXPLAIN IT.

15:45.245 --> 15:46.546
IT'S AS THOUGH...

15:46.579 --> 15:48.581
- WE'VE KNOWN EACH OTHER
ALL OUR LIVES.

15:48.615 --> 15:50.317
- EXACTLY.

15:50.350 --> 15:52.585
AS--AS IF YOU'VE BEEN
WAITING FOR ME...

15:52.619 --> 15:55.588
- AND I'VE BEEN WAITING
FOR YOU.

15:55.622 --> 15:57.457
- TWO HALVES
OF THE SAME SOUL...

15:57.490 --> 15:59.292
- THAT HAVE FINALLY MET.

15:59.326 --> 16:02.329
- IT'S WILD.

16:02.362 --> 16:06.699
LOOK, I-I KNOW THIS IS
RIDICULOUSLY FORWARD OF ME...

16:06.733 --> 16:10.003
I MEAN, I MEAN, WE
HARDLY KNOW EACH OTHER.

16:10.037 --> 16:11.404
BUT WOULD YOU MIND,

16:11.438 --> 16:16.176
THAT IS VERY MUCH, IF I--

16:16.209 --> 16:19.046
- GO RIGHT AHEAD.

16:21.481 --> 16:23.650
[moaning]

16:40.767 --> 16:43.636
[applause]

16:47.507 --> 16:49.409
- WAS THAT ALL RIGHT, MY LOVE?

16:49.442 --> 16:52.479
- IT WAS LIKE CHRISTMAS...

16:52.512 --> 16:54.647
AND NEW YEAR'S
AND MY BIRTHDAY,

16:54.681 --> 16:58.618
ALL ROLLED UP INTO ONE.

16:58.651 --> 17:01.588
- NOT THE FOURTH OF JULY?

17:01.621 --> 17:06.559
- WELL, I'M SAVING THAT
FOR YOU.

17:13.366 --> 17:15.335
- [moans]

17:15.368 --> 17:18.838
[fireworks exploding]

17:18.871 --> 17:23.543
*

17:23.576 --> 17:25.178
- I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

17:25.212 --> 17:26.579
- WHERE YOU GOING?

17:26.613 --> 17:29.782
- BATHROOM.

17:29.816 --> 17:32.285
- DO YOU THINK IT'S A GOOD IDEA
TO LET HIM GO ALONE?

17:32.319 --> 17:34.087
- WOULD YOU LIKE ME
TO HOLD IT FOR HIM?

17:34.121 --> 17:38.325
- NO, I MEAN, AFTER
WHAT HAPPENED LAST TIME.

17:38.358 --> 17:39.559
- IT'S CALLED TRUST.

17:39.592 --> 17:42.862
- YEAH, YOU CAN TRUST HE'LL
END UP IN THE EMERGENCY ROOM.

17:42.895 --> 17:44.697
- MAYBE HE WON'T.

17:44.731 --> 17:46.166
MAYBE HE'LL DISAPPOINT
ALL OF YOU

17:46.199 --> 17:49.302
AND ACTUALLY BE ALL RIGHT.

17:49.336 --> 17:51.304
- WHEN YOU WERE A BOY,

17:51.338 --> 17:55.375
DID YOU SAVE THE BIRDS
WITH THE BROKEN WINGS?

17:55.408 --> 17:57.844
- WHAT DID YOU DO,
TEAR THEM OFF?

17:57.877 --> 18:00.313
- EVERYBODY,
I WANT YOU TO MEET

18:00.347 --> 18:02.249
A VERY SPECIAL SOMEONE.

18:06.886 --> 18:08.288
- I'M BRENT.

18:08.321 --> 18:09.356
- BRENT.
- HI, BRENT.

18:09.389 --> 18:10.857
- HI.
- HI, BRENT.

18:10.890 --> 18:11.924
- HELLO, WELCOME.

18:11.958 --> 18:15.762
ANYONE WHO'S SPECIAL TO EMMETT
IS SPECIAL TO US.

18:15.795 --> 18:17.330
- WHO?

18:17.364 --> 18:18.798
- EMMETT.

18:18.831 --> 18:22.135
THAT'S ME, DARLING.

18:22.169 --> 18:23.670
- HOW LONG HAVE
YOU TWO KNOWN EACH OTHER?

18:23.703 --> 18:26.739
- WELL, IN THIS LIFE,
ONLY A BRIEF WHILE.

18:26.773 --> 18:28.775
BUT, UH, BUT I BELIEVE
THAT IN PAST LIVES,

18:28.808 --> 18:31.344
WE'VE KNOWN EACH OTHER
MANY TIMES BEFORE.

18:31.378 --> 18:32.579
DON'T YOU?

18:32.612 --> 18:33.713
- IT'S THE ONLY EXPLANATION

18:33.746 --> 18:36.149
FOR HOW WE COULD
HAVE SO MUCH IN COMMON.

18:36.183 --> 18:38.151
- YOU CAN'T BELIEVE IT.

18:38.185 --> 18:40.787
WE BOTH LOVE BRAD PITT.

18:40.820 --> 18:42.489
- CLINIQUE FOR MEN.

18:42.522 --> 18:45.225
both: ESPECIALLY WHEN
THEY'RE HAVING A SALE.

18:45.258 --> 18:47.260
- GREEN ONION-FLAVORED
POTATO CHIPS.

18:47.294 --> 18:51.298
- AND OUR FAVORITE SONG...

18:51.331 --> 18:53.633
IS SOMEWHERE OUT THERE.

18:53.666 --> 18:56.869
- NOW THAT'S UNCANNY.

18:56.903 --> 18:58.471
- WELL, COME AND HAVE
A DRINK WITH US.

18:58.505 --> 19:06.479
*

19:06.513 --> 19:08.581
HEY, WHAT'S UP?

19:10.883 --> 19:14.754
WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

19:14.787 --> 19:16.756
- EMMETT KNOWS SOME GUY
FOR ALL OF 15 MINUTES

19:16.789 --> 19:18.591
AND HE'S PRACTICALLY
A FRAT BROTHER.

19:18.625 --> 19:20.227
BLAKE YOU CAN
BARELY SPEAK TO.

19:20.260 --> 19:22.729
- WELL, MAYBE
THAT'S BECAUSE...

19:22.762 --> 19:25.398
I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO SAY.

19:25.432 --> 19:26.966
"SO, YOU NEARLY KILLED
MY FRIEND."

19:26.999 --> 19:29.569
"HEY, I HEAR YOU PASSED OUT ON
THE BATHROOM FLOOR.

19:29.602 --> 19:32.772
YOU WANT TO BE BUDS?"

19:32.805 --> 19:34.507
YOU KNOW, I FIGURED IF ANYONE
COULD'VE GIVEN HIM A CHANCE,

19:34.541 --> 19:37.244
IT WOULD'VE BEEN YOU, MICHAEL.

19:41.013 --> 19:42.249
[doorbell rings]

19:42.282 --> 19:44.484
- HOLD ON, JESUS!

19:44.517 --> 19:46.386
I'M COMING.

19:46.419 --> 19:47.554
[knocking]

19:47.587 --> 19:48.821
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

19:48.855 --> 19:50.590
- I'VE BEEN CALLING,
BUT THERE'S NO ANSWER.

19:50.623 --> 19:52.259
- OH, WE TURN THE PHONE OFF
AT NIGHT.

19:52.292 --> 19:53.660
IT WAKES GUS UP.

19:53.693 --> 19:55.395
- I'M--I'M SORRY TO BE
COMING BY SO LATE.

19:55.428 --> 19:56.563
VIC'S IN JAIL.

19:56.596 --> 19:57.830
both: WHAT?

19:57.864 --> 19:58.965
- HE SAID HE WAS AT THE MALL,

19:58.998 --> 20:00.867
HE WENT TO THE MEN'S ROOM,

20:00.900 --> 20:02.369
AND THE NEXT THING
IS THEY ARRESTED HIM

20:02.402 --> 20:03.903
FOR INDECENT EXPOSURE.

20:03.936 --> 20:05.472
- INDECENT EXPOSURE?

20:05.505 --> 20:10.310
- YEAH, HE SWEARS
HE DIDN'T DO ANYTHING.

20:10.343 --> 20:11.844
BUT HE NEEDS A LAWYER,
AND I DIDN'T KNOW WHERE TO--

20:11.878 --> 20:13.546
- NO, NO, IT'S OKAY,
I'M GOING TO GO GET DRESSED.

20:13.580 --> 20:14.714
- WELL,
IF HE DIDN'T DO ANYTHING,

20:14.747 --> 20:15.915
WHY DID THEY ARREST HIM?

20:15.948 --> 20:17.284
- IT'S HARASSMENT
OF GAY PEOPLE.

20:17.317 --> 20:19.519
COPS JUST LIKE PLAYING
"CAPTURE THE FAG."

20:19.552 --> 20:22.289
- WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?
YOU THINK VIC DID SOMETHING?

20:22.322 --> 20:23.423
- I WAS JUST ASKING--

20:23.456 --> 20:25.558
- YEAH, WELL, I'M TELLING YOU,
I KNOW MY OWN BROTHER.

20:25.592 --> 20:26.859
AND IT'S CRAP.

20:26.893 --> 20:28.060
- LISTEN,
IT'S GOING TO BE OKAY.

20:28.094 --> 20:30.597
I'M GOING TO GO GET DRESSED,
BUT WE BETTER GET A MOVE ON.

20:30.630 --> 20:32.565
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

20:38.905 --> 20:45.878
*

20:47.780 --> 20:50.817
- YOU SAID TO CHECK BACK
WITH YOU IN AN HOUR.

20:50.850 --> 20:53.052
- I STILL HAVE
EIGHT MINUTES LEFT.

20:53.085 --> 20:55.655
*

20:55.688 --> 20:59.492
- * I'M THE BOSS NOW

20:59.526 --> 21:01.528
- HE HAS ZITS ON HIS ASS,

21:01.561 --> 21:03.029
A TRAGIC ENDOWMENT,

21:03.062 --> 21:05.732
AND IS JUST GETTING OVER
A NASTY CASE OF GONORRHEA.

21:05.765 --> 21:07.033
- UH-HUH.

21:07.066 --> 21:08.768
- * I'M THE BOSS NOW

21:08.801 --> 21:10.870
* HEY, HEY

21:10.903 --> 21:13.440
- WELL, IF I WERE YOU,
I WOULDN'T WAIT TOO LONG.

21:13.473 --> 21:16.075
BY THEN
I MAY HAVE OTHER PLANS.

21:16.108 --> 21:17.877
*

21:17.910 --> 21:19.746
- * I'M STRONGER NOW

21:21.681 --> 21:26.386
- SO WHAT'S WITH YOU ANYWAY?

21:26.419 --> 21:27.787
- NOTHING.

21:27.820 --> 21:33.493
- WHO'S YOUR, UH, FRIEND?

21:33.526 --> 21:34.661
- NOBODY.

21:34.694 --> 21:36.863
- YOU LOOK PRETTY TIGHT TO ME.

21:36.896 --> 21:40.066
SO HOW COME YOU DIDN'T
INTRODUCE US?

21:40.099 --> 21:42.068
- HE WOULDN'T LIKE YOU.

21:42.101 --> 21:44.437
- MAYBE HE WOULD IF I, UH...

21:44.471 --> 21:45.738
OFFERED HIM A FAVOR.

21:45.772 --> 21:46.973
- YEAH, WELL,
HE'S NOT INTERESTED

21:47.006 --> 21:50.309
IN ANY OF YOUR FAVORS.

21:53.780 --> 21:56.716
- GREAT STUFF.

21:56.749 --> 21:58.518
GREAT PRICE.

22:03.656 --> 22:05.592
- AND I TOLD YOU,
NEITHER AM I.

22:08.961 --> 22:12.932
- * I'M THE BOSS NOW

22:12.965 --> 22:15.602
* I'M THE BOSS NOW

22:15.635 --> 22:17.737
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

22:17.770 --> 22:19.672
- PROBABLY JUST
WHAT IT LOOKS LIKE,

22:19.706 --> 22:21.641
LOITERING OUTSIDE
THE MEN'S ROOM.

22:21.674 --> 22:23.910
- DID YOU COME
TO CHECK UP ON ME?

22:23.943 --> 22:25.845
- COURSE NOT.

22:25.878 --> 22:27.580
I JUST SEEM TO MEET
THE CUTEST GUYS HERE.

22:27.614 --> 22:30.483
- 'CAUSE I TOLD YOU,
I'M FINE.

22:36.188 --> 22:38.758
- I KNOW.

22:43.496 --> 22:45.632
- COME ON, LET'S, UH...

22:45.665 --> 22:47.634
GO FIND THE OTHERS.

22:47.667 --> 22:50.102
- LET'S NOT.

22:50.136 --> 22:53.005
I'D RATHER JUST BE WITH YOU.

22:53.039 --> 22:54.741
- GENTLEMEN PREFER BLONDES,

22:54.774 --> 22:57.610
AND THIS BLONDE PREFERS
GENTLEMEN IN LEATHER.

22:57.644 --> 23:00.713
A BIG HAND FOR DWAYNE.

23:00.747 --> 23:03.883
[cheers and applause]

23:03.916 --> 23:11.891
*

23:16.596 --> 23:19.899
[Tchaikovsky's
Nutcracker Suite]

23:19.932 --> 23:23.636
- I'VE ALWAYS DREAMT ABOUT
LIVING IN A LITTLE COTTAGE.

23:23.670 --> 23:25.505
- WITH A GARDEN OUT BACK?

23:25.538 --> 23:29.442
- WHERE I CAN GROW
LAVENDER AND DAFFODILS,

23:29.476 --> 23:30.777
AND WEAR A BIG SUN BONNET,

23:30.810 --> 23:33.713
LIKE MY AUNT BELLE,
THAT TIES UNDER THE CHIN.

23:33.746 --> 23:35.815
- AND WE'LL COOK
GOURMET MEALS.

23:35.848 --> 23:38.685
- SEASONED WITH
OUR VERY OWN HERBS.

23:38.718 --> 23:41.788
- AND ON SNOWY EVENINGS, WE'LL
CURL UP IN FRONT OF THE FIRE

23:41.821 --> 23:44.591
WITH BIG MUGS OF HOT TEA.

23:44.624 --> 23:46.192
- AND--AND IN THE SUMMER,

23:46.225 --> 23:48.728
WE'LL TAKE LONG, LAZY WALKS

23:48.761 --> 23:53.165
DOWN A SUN-DAPPLED
COUNTRY LANE.

23:56.769 --> 23:58.705
- IT'S HEAVEN.

23:58.738 --> 24:01.841
- BLISS.

24:04.577 --> 24:06.546
- I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

24:06.579 --> 24:08.080
DON'T GO AWAY.

24:08.114 --> 24:11.884
- I'LL BE WAITING RIGHT HERE.

24:11.918 --> 24:19.859
*

24:24.697 --> 24:27.667
[techno music]

24:27.700 --> 24:30.803
*

24:30.837 --> 24:33.840
- YOU HAD ENOUGH PULSATING,
GRINDING FLESH FOR ONE EVENING?

24:33.873 --> 24:35.241
- I'M READY TO GO
WHENEVER YOU ARE.

24:35.274 --> 24:37.243
- NO, YOU CAN'T LEAVE YET.

24:37.276 --> 24:38.811
YOU'LL MISS MY BIG NUMBER.

24:38.845 --> 24:40.947
- OH, RIGHT, LIKE YOU'D
REALLY GO THROUGH WITH IT.

24:40.980 --> 24:42.982
- WELL, IF YOU LEAVE NOW,
YOU'LL NEVER KNOW.

24:43.015 --> 24:44.116
- DWAYNE!

24:44.150 --> 24:48.054
[cheers and applause]

24:48.087 --> 24:50.122
IF DWAYNE BECOMES KING,

24:50.156 --> 24:53.726
HE'LL BE THE RULER BY WHOM
ALL OTHERS ARE MEASURED.

24:53.760 --> 24:56.295
I OUGHT TO KNOW,
I MEASURED HIM MYSELF.

24:56.328 --> 24:58.565
[laughter and cheers]

24:58.598 --> 25:02.602
RIGHT. OUR NEXT CONTESTANT
LIKES YOUNGER MEN.

25:02.635 --> 25:05.872
HIS FAVORITE PASTIME
IS FEELING SUPERIOR.

25:05.905 --> 25:08.575
HIS SPECIAL SKILL
IS MANIPULATING PEOPLE.

25:08.608 --> 25:09.576
[scattered boos]

25:09.609 --> 25:10.777
- MUST BE YOU.

25:10.810 --> 25:12.078
- LET'S PUT OUR HANDS TOGETHER

25:12.111 --> 25:15.014
FOR PITTSBURGH'S HUNKIEST
CHIROPRACTOR,

25:15.047 --> 25:17.083
DR. DAVID CAMERON!

25:17.116 --> 25:21.120
[cheers and applause]

25:21.153 --> 25:23.990
- YOU ASSHOLE.

25:24.023 --> 25:25.725
- DR. CAMERON.

25:25.758 --> 25:27.059
PAGING DR. CAMERON.

25:27.093 --> 25:28.895
- I THOUGHT YOU WERE
SIGNING UP YOURSELF.

25:28.928 --> 25:30.863
- NOW WHY WOULD
I WANT TO DO THAT,

25:30.897 --> 25:32.298
WHEN YOU KNOW
I FIND THIS OBSESSION

25:32.331 --> 25:35.802
WITH YOUTH AND ABS AND SEX
SO APPALLING?

25:35.835 --> 25:37.336
- YOU DON'T HAVE
TO GO UP THERE.

25:37.369 --> 25:39.238
- DON'T WORRY,
I HAVE NO INTENTION OF IT.

25:39.271 --> 25:41.173
- THANK GOD.

25:41.207 --> 25:42.942
YOU WOULDN'T WANT TO MAKE
A FOOL OF YOURSELF

25:42.975 --> 25:45.745
DANCING AROUND
IN YOUR UNDERWEAR AT YOUR AGE.

25:45.778 --> 25:49.115
- DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT, DOC,
IT WAS JUST A JOKE.

25:49.148 --> 25:51.751
- WELL, YOU THINK
I CAN'T DO IT?

25:51.784 --> 25:52.752
AT MY AGE?

25:52.785 --> 25:54.654
- PAGING DR. CAMERON!

25:54.687 --> 25:55.855
OH, PFFT...

25:55.888 --> 25:58.925
MOTHER OF GOD!

25:58.958 --> 26:00.793
DR. CAMERON?

26:00.827 --> 26:03.129
[cheering]

26:09.101 --> 26:12.939
crowd: DR. CAMERON!
DR. CAMERON!

26:12.972 --> 26:14.874
[chanting continues]

26:14.907 --> 26:16.342
- DAVID.

26:16.375 --> 26:17.910
[chanting continues]

26:20.112 --> 26:23.082
[club music]

26:23.115 --> 26:31.057
*

27:16.435 --> 27:18.671
- WHOA.

27:18.705 --> 27:21.974
[cheering]

27:53.940 --> 27:56.275
[wild cheering]

27:59.946 --> 28:02.081
- HE ISN'T.

28:02.114 --> 28:04.016
[cheering]

28:04.050 --> 28:05.417
- YES, HE IS.

28:05.451 --> 28:07.253
[cheering]

28:07.286 --> 28:09.021
- WHOA.

28:13.960 --> 28:16.729
- OW!

28:16.763 --> 28:17.730
*

28:17.764 --> 28:21.968
- OH, HEY.

28:26.172 --> 28:28.875
- YOU WANNA COME WITH ME?
- WHERE ARE WE GOING?

28:28.908 --> 28:30.409
- WELL, I TALKED
TO YOUR LAWYER.

28:30.442 --> 28:32.244
- EXCUSE ME, SERGEANT?
WE'RE HERE TO SEE--

28:32.278 --> 28:33.813
- VICTOR GRASSI.

28:33.846 --> 28:35.447
- GRASSI.

28:35.481 --> 28:37.216
OH, UH, SORRY, LADIES.

28:37.249 --> 28:39.318
YOU HAVE TO COME BACK LATER.
HE'S STILL BEING PROCESSED.

28:39.351 --> 28:40.486
- BUT I'M HIS SISTER.

28:40.519 --> 28:41.587
- AND I'M
MR. GRASSI'S ATTORNEY.

28:41.620 --> 28:44.256
COULD YOU JUST TELL ME HOW MUCH
HIS BAIL IS SET AT?

28:44.290 --> 28:46.358
- $5,000.

28:46.392 --> 28:48.294
- WHAT?
- $5,000?

28:48.327 --> 28:50.362
- ISN'T THAT HIGH
FOR A FIRST OFFENSE?

28:50.396 --> 28:52.231
- SAYS HERE HE'S GOT
A PREVIOUS ARREST.

28:52.264 --> 28:53.766
- FOR WHAT?

28:53.800 --> 28:56.836
- POSSESSION OF
AN ILLEGAL SUBSTANCE.

28:56.869 --> 28:59.338
- [sighs]

29:03.542 --> 29:08.214
- HE WAS PULLED OVER.
IT WAS TEN YEARS AGO.

29:08.247 --> 29:11.183
THERE WAS A JOINT
IN THE GLOVE COMPARTMENT.

29:11.217 --> 29:13.052
IT WASN'T EVEN HIS.

29:13.085 --> 29:15.554
- THEN WHY DIDN'T HE
SAY SOMETHING?

29:15.587 --> 29:17.790
- BECAUSE EVEN WHEN
WE WERE KIDS,

29:17.824 --> 29:20.159
HE NEVER SQUEALED ON ME.

29:23.162 --> 29:24.864
LOOK, OFFICER.

29:24.897 --> 29:26.565
MY BROTHER'S VERY SICK.

29:26.598 --> 29:28.434
HE'S GOT TO TAKE HIS MEDS.

29:28.467 --> 29:30.136
- WHAT'S WRONG WITH HIM?

29:30.169 --> 29:31.838
- HE'S H.I.V. POSITIVE.

29:31.871 --> 29:34.506
- OH, FIGURES.
- EXCUSE ME?

29:34.540 --> 29:36.142
- NO DRUGS ALLOWED
IN THE HOLDING CELL

29:36.175 --> 29:37.877
UNTIL THE PRECINCT DOCTORS
EXAMINE HIM.

29:37.910 --> 29:39.278
- BUT THESE ARE
PRESCRIPTION MEDICATIONS.

29:39.311 --> 29:40.847
HIS LIFE DEPENDS ON IT.

29:40.880 --> 29:42.281
- WELL, IF HE'S SO SICK,
WHAT WAS HE DOING

29:42.314 --> 29:43.582
HANGING OUT
IN A PUBLIC MEN'S ROOM?

29:43.615 --> 29:46.018
- TAKING A PISS.

29:46.052 --> 29:49.388
- JESUS.
COME ON.

29:55.394 --> 29:58.130
*

29:58.164 --> 30:01.901
- OW, AH!

30:01.934 --> 30:03.169
- YOU ARE SO CUTE.

30:03.202 --> 30:04.971
- YOU HAVE GREAT ABS.

30:05.004 --> 30:06.906
- UH, WELL, THEY'RE--
THEY'RE ESSENTIAL FOR, UH,

30:06.939 --> 30:08.574
STRONG BACK SUPPORT
AND GOOD POSTURE.

30:08.607 --> 30:10.309
- CALL ME.
- YEAH, PLEASE.

30:10.342 --> 30:11.443
- ANYTIME.

30:11.477 --> 30:13.379
- I'LL MAKE IT
SO WORTH YOUR WHILE.

30:13.412 --> 30:15.848
- DO YOU MIND?

30:15.882 --> 30:19.051
HE'S ALREADY TAKEN.

30:19.085 --> 30:21.353
WELL, I SUPPOSE
YOU'RE PLEASED WITH YOURSELF.

30:21.387 --> 30:22.588
WIPE THAT GRIN OFF YOUR FACE.

30:22.621 --> 30:24.623
PUT YOUR SHIRT ON!
- MICHAEL...

30:24.656 --> 30:26.458
- I DON'T WANT TO HEAR
ANOTHER WORD ABOUT IT.

30:26.492 --> 30:27.459
COME HERE.

30:27.493 --> 30:35.467
*

31:00.059 --> 31:02.394
- CAN I ENTER THE CONTEST?

31:02.428 --> 31:04.363
YEAH.

31:08.467 --> 31:12.038
- MAY I HAVE YOUR ATTENTION,
BOYS AND BOYS?

31:12.071 --> 31:15.607
THE NEXT CONTESTANT LOVES
THE POWERPUFF GIRLS,

31:15.641 --> 31:19.645
MARGARITAS, AND OLDER MEN
WHO TAKE HIM FOR GRANTED.

31:19.678 --> 31:21.981
HERE'S JUSTIN!

31:22.014 --> 31:24.416
[cheers and applause]

